<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-14993] Catch&#160;CorruptSSTableExceptions and FSErrors in&#160;ALAExecutorService</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-14993</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Actively handling CorruptSSTableExceptions and FSErrors currently only happens during opening of sstables and in the default exception handler. What&apos;s missing is to catch these in AbstractLocalAwareExecutorService as well. Therefor I propose to add calls to FileUtils.handleCorruptSSTable/handleFSError there, too, so we don&apos;t miss invoking the disk failure policy in that case.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13210966">CASSANDRA-14993</key>
            <summary>Catch&#160;CorruptSSTableExceptions and FSErrors in&#160;ALAExecutorService</summary>
